late december was found on june 19 fathers day said his wife 
lauri nauditt 
he always wanted to own his own business and this was 
something that excited him mrs nauditt said recently 
he had never been stung until april she said the week 
before he died he was stung once and his finger swelled up but 
he didnt think anything about it 
nationally 41 people died from insect stings in 1985 the last 
year for which national figures are known according to the 
washington department of vital statistics 
