<TEXT>
a city councilman stood up for senior 
citizens who want to sit down and the result was a law requiring 
comfortable seating in the lobbies of most apartment buildings for 
the elderly 
the city ordinance guarantees that the elderly who want to see 
something beyond their four walls have a place to go officials 
said thursday the law requires lounge chairs sofas or benches 
with backs to be padded 
complaints by senior citizens prompted the city council to pass 
the ordinance for all subsidized buildings with at least 30 
residents said maynard banks the deputy director of the jersey 
city housing authority 
glenn cunningham the president of the city council said he 
sponsored the law because one building replaced comfortable seats 
with hard benches in an effort to discourage senior citizens from 
congregating 
they claimed theyd have to clean the area but i felt it was 
very insensitive cunningham said many seniors have back 
ailments and if youre waiting for a bus it can be painful to sit 
down for a halfhour it was cruel and unfair 
we were in full agreement with the law said maria maio 
director of development in the citys housing and economic 
development department seniors like to sit in the lobby or 
outside thats where the action is 
you bet said josephine rice president of the senior citizens 
club at the plaza apartments 
they enjoy the lounge ms rice said leaving her card game 
in the lobby thats where they watch tv we also play bingo 
there 
apartment manager mary johnson likes the law but suspects 
comfortable seating also means she has to watch her step in the 
lobby of her building 
theyre parked there all day ms johnson said with a laugh 
they like to see whos coming in and going out its the best 
place to be to watch what everybody is doing 
