the producer rice price under the new price producers will 
receive 127 for every 132 pounds of rice 
after going through japans complex distribution system rice 
costs about 4 a pound 
analysts pointed to excess rice production in the past few years 
and the declining consumption as reasons for the price decline 
more than 18 million tons of rice are stockpiled 
excess production is the direct motivation to lower the 
price said masatsune adachi an agricultural analyst 
but the bottom line is the appreciation of the yen the 
agricultural ministry wants japanese rice production competitive 
enough to endure foreign competition in case foreign demands to 
open the market is extended to rice adachi said 
rice is japans top agricultural product the government 
