rescuers digging through tons of 
concrete and twisted steel for the victims of a department store 
collapse today rescued six people and worked to free others 
believed alive at least 11 people were killed and 47 injured 
two women a 2yearold girl a boy and girl both aged 8 and a 
14yearold girl were rescued during the morning at least one 
survivor was still trapped more than 20 hours after the disaster 
officials said 
the 2yearold appeared to have been protected by some other 
people around her who are believed dead said lt victor 
rodriguez of the citys police department 
