consulate on monday stopped processing soviet refugees most of 
whom are armenians for travel to the united states 
we want to emphasize this is only a postponement of 
departure us ambassador jack matlock told reporters 
matlock said the us government had run out of money to 
resettle soviet refugees for this fiscal year which ends sept 30 
the process is to resume oct 1 when a new fiscal year begins ms 
squire said 
the embassy in june gave permission to a record 2063 soviets 
94 percent of whom are armenians to immigrate to the united 
states that was more than all of fiscal year 1987 
the us government has made soviet emigration restrictions a 
key human rights issue in relations between the two countries and 
the soviets have eased their policy to permit thousands of citizens 
who claim family ties in the west to leave the country 
we are ready to start a new life in a new country and what 
happens asked sarafyan already they are deceiving us 
