<TEXT>
britain announced friday it had signed its 
biggestever arms deal with saudi arabia supplanting the united 
states as the major arms supplier to the oilrich kingdom 
a defense ministry statement gave no details but official 
sources said the deal which includes mine sweepers and some 50 
tornado fighters was worth more than 17 billion that dwarfed a 
75 billion contract won by britain in 1986 to supply saudi arabia 
with 72 tornado fighters and other aircraft 
the ministry statement said the deal signed sunday in a 
memorandum of understanding was a new phase of the previous 
contract and involved the supply of additional aircraft a 
construction program and specialized navy vessels 
it included an economic offset program the statement said 
apparently meaning an agreement to step up british investment in 
saudi arabia 
in the saudi capital of riyadh a brief official saudi statement 
confirmed a deal was signed that would provide significant 
enhancement of the existing defense capabilities of saudi arabia 
the deal a huge boost for the british armaments industry in the 
next decade followed years of british lobbying 
unlike the us administration prime minister margaret 
thatchers government is not constrained by lawmakers protesting 
that weapons sales to saudi arabia may endanger or offend israel 
official sources said the agreement involved the supply of 50 to 
60 tornado aircraft 50 to 60 hawk jet training aircraft six mine 
sweepers for use in the persian gulf 90 helicopters weapons 
systems and the construction of two tornado bases 
the contract also included several civil aircraft for use by the 
saudi royal family said the sources speaking on condition of 
anonymity 
british aerospace lead contractor for the tornados which it 
manufacturers with west german and italian companies also will 
build the two tornado bases the sources said the bases will be at 
dhahran to cover oil installations in the persian gulf and near 
the saudi capital riyadh the sources said 
the other major british companies involved are westland 
helicopters and vosper thorneycroft makers of sandown class mine 
sweepers 
british sources said the saudis have ordered westlands new 
black hawk helicopter 
defense sources said detailed contracts for the whole package 
still had to be negotiated 
legislator sir antony buck chairman of the governing 
conservative partys defense committee said the agreement was an 
important breakthrough especially as the various pieces of 
equipment were in hot competition from the french and others 
britain has a long history of arms links with saudi arabia and 
mrs thatcher has cultivated the relationship since coming to power 
in 1979 
this included apologizing in 1980 to saudi arabia after 
television companies refused to bow to british government pressure 
not to screen a film death of a princess the fictional story 
about the execution of a saudi princess and her lover offended the 
