<TEXT>
president lee tenghui rose to the top of 
the ruling nationalist party as the handpicked successor to chiang 
chingkuo the strongman leader who in his final days began to 
bring democratic change to this prosperous island 
lee 65 is the first native taiwanese to lead the nationalist 
party or kuomintang which was formed 94 years ago on the chinese 
mainland by sun yatsen and still claims to be the legitimate ruler 
of all china 
he became president and acting party chairman after the jan 13 
death of chiang the son of chiang kaishek ended four decades of 
family rule on taiwan 
chiang chingkuo had chosen lee to be his vice president in 1984 
over several more prominent native taiwanese officials 
lee a lowkey vice president quickly gained popularity after 
ascending to the presidency frequently touring the island 
he also showed respect to the oldguard nationalist officials 
who arrived from mainland china in 1949 with chiang kaishek by 
frequently consulting with them 
taiwanese respect and love him and mainlanders dare not 
defame him said peng huaien associate professor of politics at 
chinese culture university 
lee has vowed support for the liberalization program begun by 
chiang chingkuo who lifted martial law ended a ban on opposition 
parties and promised to give taiwanese a greater say in the 
government long dominated by nationalists from the chinese mainland 
who lost a civil war to the communists 
the new party leader an agricultural economic expert also has 
questioned taiwans conservative financial policies 
lee has moved cautiously however to not antagonize elderly 
nationalist conservatives wary about the quick pace of change 
chiang chingkuo introduced 
political analysts describe lee as a tactful politician a keen 
student of japanese fencing known as kendo lee has told visitors 
he beat more than 100 challengers in high school by prevailing 
over a move by remaining still meaning to wait for the opponent 
to make the first move 
at the age of 42 he left his teaching post at a taiwan 
university to study in the united states where he earned a 
doctorate from cornell university 
he has published several works on agriculture and economics 
a christian lee is married and has two daughters he plays golf 
and plays the violin 
