bhopal gas disaster 
the petition challenged an order issued by a panel of the madhya 
pradesh high court on april 4 that union carbide corp be required 
to pay 192 million in relief to victims of the 1984 gas leak at a 
carbide subsidiary plant 
a trial court in bhopal earlier had set payments at 269 million 
union carbide also has asked the full madhya pradesh high court 
to review the interim relief order contending that any demand for 
payments before the overall damage suit is resolved would be unfair 
india is suing union carbide for 3 billion in damages stemming 
from the leak of toxic methyl isocyanate gas from a pesticide plant 
in bhopal on dec 3 1984 the case is in preliminary hearings in 
bhopal in central india 
nearly 3000 people were killed and more than 20000 seriously 
injured by the gas it is considered the worlds worst industrial 
disaster 
the petition filed friday said the high court failed to 
appreciate that in a tragedy of this nature grant of interim 
relief need not be determined with mathematical accuracy 
it added if the trial court adopted and arrived at the figure 
by applying its judicial mind on the facts of the case there will 
be no justifying ground for interfering with the quantum by the 
high court 
the statement also said that damages that may be ultimately 
decreed are bound to be far in excess of the interim relief granted 
by the trial court 
no date was set for hearing the petition 
</TEXT>
