likely that this factor will be considered not just possible but 
probable 
the labor department itself seems to suggest that much in 
pointing out that about threequarters of the increase in jobs came 
in the 16 to 24yearold age group 
another factor one that has occurred before could be involved 
in the may count civilian employment dropped by 518000 jobs 
in june employment rose by 823000 did such a extreme dip and 
rise actually occur or was there a bug in the methodology 
dont jump to conclusions about imminent inflation even if 
some of the socalled authorities do 
