order he issued at the governments request last week and which had 
been due to expire friday the order barred the executive board 
from either making large expenditures of union funds or destroying 
union records 
federal prosecutors had sought a preliminary injunction that 
among other things would have created one or more courtappointed 
liaison officers to police corruption among the hundreds of locals 
in the 16 millionmember union 
