only some phone lines and united parcel service the biggest 
expense was advertising oneninth of a page in byte magazine in 
february 1982 
the phone didnt ring for three days and we sat looking at 
each other gallup recalled then it started and never stopped 
we did everything took calls placed orders packed boxes 
when we were in business a year we knew it would require 100 
percent of our attention 
they left the audio business to halls family hired eight more 
people they now employ 185 and rented space at the inn before 
long the phone company had to upgrade the lines to keene the 
