<TEXT>
continental corp one of the worlds leading 
insurance concerns disclosed plans friday to sell two life 
insurance subsidiaries for a total of 213 million as part of a 
previously announced divestment 
the commercial life unit will be sold to two companies kaufman 
amp broad inc and unum corp for 179 million in cash kaufman amp 
broad will get commercial lifes annuity reserve business and unum 
will take the units other businesses continental said in a 
statement 
in addition continental will sell its loyalty life unit to a 
group of unidentified private investors for cash and securities 
totaling about 34 million the company said 
based in new york continental is one of the worlds largest 
insurance organizations with 5 billion in revenues and operations 
in more than 100 countries the company announced intentions last 
september to divest its life insurance subsidiaries 
in april the company sold its national life assurance co of 
canada unit 
</TEXT>
