<TEXT>
marvel entertainment group the comic book 
home of spiderman the incredible hulk and captain america has 
been put up for sale by new world entertainment ltd the company 
announced thursday 
new world the movie and toy company that acquired marvel for a 
reported 40 million to 50 million in november 1986 said it would 
sell all or part of marvel entertainment group 
marvel with comic book headquarters in new york and a tv 
animation and production division in los angeles makes animated 
cartoon series as well as comics it also publishes childrens 
comics and books 
new world which did not give a reason for the sale also 
announced it expects a secondquarter operating loss of 25 million 
before taxes 
the company blamed the anticipated losses on boxoffice failure 
of its three movies 18 again dead heat and wrong 
guys on high overhead and debt service and disappointing video 
sales 
</TEXT>
