<TEXT>
police reported thursday they have arrested former 
bank of boston vice president max buteau and charged him with 
conspiring to defraud the bank 
wayne taylor a bank of boston spokesman in boston said the 
total amount involved in the alleged fraud was about 29 million 
scotland yard said in a statement that the 39yearold buteau 
was accused of issuing false guarantees of payment to foreign and 
domestic corporations to enable funds to be drawn against them 
between oct 21 last year and feb 16 this year 
scotland yard said buteau who lives in london was arrested 
wednesday 
taylor said buteau who worked at the banks branch at victoria 
in central london resigned last month 
</TEXT>
