<TEXT>
bf goodrich co announced thursday that it 
had signed a letter of intent to sell a majority of units in its 
fabricated polymers division to richard fasenmyer the divisions 
president 
fasenmyer will acquire commercial wallcovering rubber and 
plastic matting tank lining industrial and commercial extrusion 
units and a variety of other specialty rubber and plastic producing 
units 
terms of the agreement contingent on its approval by the 
goodrich board of directors were not disclosed 
the sale of most of our fabricated polymers division means 
that we have now disposed of the last of our former industrial 
products businesses said leigh carter goodrich president and 
chief operating officer these businesses clearly did not fit 
into our strategy since we are now focusing on chemical and 
aerospace operations 
the facilities involved had 1987 sales of about 80 million and 
employ 750 people at plants in akron marietta cincinnati and 
columbus ohio modesto calif and livonia mich 
</TEXT>
